    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) represents a pinnacle of analog driver feedback. Powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six paired with a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle, this example is mechanically impeccable. It features a factory-spec limited-slip differential and a meticulously maintained suspension utilizing MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear geometry for superlative lateral grip. The braking system remains razor-sharp with four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and a recent bore-scope inspection confirms zero scoring. The undercarriage is remarkably dry, reflecting a life of climate-controlled storage and rigorous maintenance. Original Arctic Silver Metallic paint shows consistent depth readings across all panels, confirming its untouched status.",
